As I’ve mentioned earlier that sports act as a backbone for country’s economy and reputation. 
Extreme sports is one of the things that can not only attract global tourism in Pakistan but also open doors for foreign investors in Pakistan.
Currently Pakistan is facing an economical crunch with a major dip in the tourism industry that’s discouraging investors to invest in extreme sports and vacational activities in Pakistan. 
Extreme Sports not only fascinates a larger audience (globally) but also resonates the nations power and willingness to rise up. 
For any declining nation I believe it’s very important to invest in their local athletes, they won’t only bring medals to the country but also improve its reputation and put the country on map for investors globally. 

I look forward to represent Pakistan in the 2025 Skydiving World Championship.

Lots of prayers required. 🤲🏻
